snippet.textDisplay: It irritates me that they have to say, "don't panic".  Feelings of worry is a natural human condition and this situation will have an impact on livelihoods and earnings.  Many live from week to week and have families to feed, so it's crushing, therefore it can't resonate well being told how to feel.  Besides, people have a right to go through the motions of feeling.  The first reaction of panic or worry causes us to move to the next, which is take action.  There’s nothing wrong with that.  Now, with that said, I would agree that stockpiling goods isn't a panic action that I'd recommend.  We all choose how we manage our feelings, and what action we take but don't feed us condescending advice.
